## Description
The&nbsp;**Transform Content (DT)** task allows to&nbsp;process input data&nbsp;using the Doxee Platform 2 Data Transformation software service.

## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the&nbsp;**Alias** field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- Click on the **Resource** field to select the Data Transformation resource to use.

> Note

For more information,&nbsp;see:&nbsp;

[Data Transformation Program Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/data-transformation-program-resource-reference)

- [Data Transformation Project Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/data-transformation-project-resource-reference)

> Tip

If you select a Data Transformation Project resource, click **Preset**&nbsp;to automatically import the Reader and Writer configuration from the DT project. The Writer's output filename will not be imported.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The endpoint used to access the Data Transformation service is:*&nbsp;&lt;site endpoint&gt;/&lt;portal path&gt;/dt/&lt;operation path&gt;*.

- *(optional)* To add an&nbsp;**Input Reader**, click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) and fill in the required fields.![](data:image/png;base64,)

Enter the&nbsp;**Name** of the reader.

> Important

This field is case sensitive.

- *(optional)*&nbsp;Enter the filename&nbsp;**Pattern** to filter the files to use (for example: *.csv).

> Known Issue

Due to a known issue, the input filter specified in the **Pattern** field&nbsp;does not work correctly based on the defined regular expressions (for example, if you enter the "**.xml*" filter, an input file named *file.xml* is not recognized). The suggested workaround for input files that do not have a predefined name is to enter an asterisk character: *****.

- Select the&nbsp;**Format** of the input file. The available options are:

**FLAT**

- **XML**

- **AFP**

- Select the&nbsp;**Separator** used in the input file. The available options are:

**LF**

- **CR**

- **CRLF**

- Select the required file&nbsp;**Encoding** from the drop-down menu (default value: UTF-8).

- *(optional)*&nbsp;To add an&nbsp;**Input Catalog**, click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) and select an element:![](data:image/png;base64,)The available options are:

**File**: Allows to use component catalogs created by a previous task in the workflow or from an input package

- **Resource**: Allows to use an Asset resource (see [Asset Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/asset-resource-reference))

> Important

The catalog&nbsp;must be in CSV format.

- Enter the&nbsp;**Name** of the catalog.

> Important

This field is case sensitive.

- *(mandatory) *Enter the **Pattern** or **Resource** to use for the catalog.

Input catalog type

Field

Description

File

**Pattern**

Enter the filename to filter the files to use (for example: *.csv)

> Known Issue

Due to a known issue, the input filter specified in the **Pattern** field&nbsp;does not work correctly based on the defined regular expressions (for example, if you enter the "**.xml*" filter, an input file named *file.xml* is not recognized). The suggested workaround for input files that do not have a predefined name is to enter an asterisk character: *****.

Resource

**Resource**

Select an Asset resource to use (see [Asset Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/asset-resource-reference)).

Enable the&nbsp;**Optional** toggle to indicate that the catalog is optional.

- *(optional)* To add an&nbsp;**Output&nbsp;Writer**, click ![](data:image/png;base64,)&nbsp;(**Add**) and fill in the required fields.![](data:image/png;base64,)

Enter the&nbsp;**Name** of the writer (default value: *output.xml*).

> Important

This field is case sensitive.

- Enter the **Filename**&nbsp;to use for the output file.

- Select the required file&nbsp;**Encoding**&nbsp;from the drop-down menu (default value: UTF-8).

- In the&nbsp;**Discards Filename** field, enter the name of the discard file to be generated (default value: "discard").

- *(optional)&nbsp;*In the**&nbsp;Attributes** section, you may add up to 10 custom attributes to be added to the generated output file:

**{{Account name}}**

- **{{Account alias}}**

- **{{Job name}}**

- **{{Job number}}**

- **{{Job scope}}**

- **{{Step alias}}**

- **{{Tenant name}}**

- **{{Tenant alias}}**

- **{{Tenant stage}}**

> Tip

You may use any additional parameters specified in the request as attributes, in the following format: **{{parameter}}**.

> Important

After adding&nbsp;10 custom attributes,&nbsp;you cannot add any more unless you delete one of the configured attributes.

- In the&nbsp;**Flags** field, select the execution options:

**Relaxed**:&nbsp;Skip the notification of some errors.

- **Debug**: Log all errors and include detailed information on the errors, specifically errors that occur during execution of the Data Mapper.

- **Legacy**: Use the legacy Data Mangler (retro-compatibility mode).

- *(optional)* Enable&nbsp;**Analytics** tracking.

## Warmup
When using a Data Transformation resource in an On-Demand Workflow, **the first file in alphabetical order** among those saved in the **default preview profile** inside the Data Transformation resource will be used during the deployment of the Workflow to warm up the service. In this way it is possible to provide a quick response already from the first request.This means that the first file must be small or in any case in line with the type of standard input that is expected and must not fail when executed.
